The paper deals with privacy implications of social media data sharing and proposes a person recognition system that can handle variations in pose and clothing. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves analysis of large volumes of data, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the experimental results, which could be relevant to social and information sciences (cs.SI).
